  <scopecontent id="aspace_5bb4d18daab3a1aba4b2c13dab601ead">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Includes correspondence pertaining to a course on patent law at Cornell, 1907-1908; correpondence between Irvine and other law school administrators in New York State, primarily concerning the New York Association of Law Instructors and its interest in the examination for and admission to the New York State Bar; minutes of a meeting of the association; and copies of speeches and other printed material.</p>  </scopecontent>
